      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative metric (e.g., validation metric V or E%) must be reported for each QoI against experimental data.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute percentage error for hemolysis index is 11.4% across five operating points; pressure head error below 4.2%. Both within acceptance bands defined for MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must map directly to the clinical decision metric (absolute hemolysis index).",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) computed from both CFD and bench experiments; same formula applied in both contexts ensuring direct relevance to COU decision threshold."
